President Donald J. Trump signed an Executive Order on May 11, 2017, establishing the Presidential Advisory Commission on Election Integrity. Vice President Mike Pence chairs the Commission, and Kansas Secretary of State Kris Kobach serves as the vice chair. The Commission's meeting on September 12, 2017, at the New Hampshire Institute of Politics (NHIOP) at Saint Anselm College will be livestreamed for remote viewing. Press credentials for the meeting can be requested, but approval is not guaranteed due to limited space. Written comments from the public can be submitted for the Commission's consideration through the Federal eRulemaking portal or via mail. The Commission's purpose is to study the registration and voting processes used in Federal elections and submit a report to the President identifying laws and practices that enhance or undermine the integrity of the voting processes, as well as vulnerabilities in voting systems that could lead to improper voter registrations and fraudulent voting.